3E%3Cli%3EThe%20app%20is%20starting%20with%20true%20crime%20and%20aims%20to%20branch%20out%20to%20other%20genres%20soon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20movies%20designed%20for%20your%20phone%20are%20getting%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20Hollywood%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrueShort%2C%20which%20makes%20AI%20%26quot%3Bverticals%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0movies%20chopped%20up%20into%20one-%20to%20three-minute%20episodes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0has%20gathered%20a%20who's%20who%20of%20backers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20startup%20has%20raised%20%2412%20million%20in%20seed%20funding%20led%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkeith-rabois-ai-impact-tech-jobs-product-manager-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKeith%20Rabois%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20exclusively%20learned.%20Also%20participating%20in%20the%20round%20were%20Jeffrey%20Katzenberg's%20WndrCo%2C%20A24's%20Ravi%20Nandan%2C%20Behance%20founder%20Scott%20Belsky%2C%20and%20General%20Catalyst.%20The%20company's%20founding%20creative%20partner%20is%20W.%20Hayden%20Schwartz%2C%20formerly%20of%20Legendary%20Entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrueShort%20was%20started%20last%20year%20by%20Nate%20Tepper%2C%20a%20serial%20entrepreneur%20who%20founded%20Humans%20Anonymous%2C%20a%20mental%20health%20app%3B%20Set%20The%20Set%2C%20a%20song%20request%20app%3B%20and%20UNight%2C%20a%20meet-up%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETepper%20said%20he%20had%20long%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20Hollywood%20film%20but%20knew%20finances%20would%20be%20a%20limiting%20factor.%20Then%20he%20saw%20the%20explosion%20of%20low-budget%20%26quot%3Bmicro%20dramas%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0another%20name%20for%20verticals%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20mobile%20apps%20like%20ReelShort%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdramabox-strategy-to-dominate-us-micro-dramas-creators-disney-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eand%20DramaBox%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20recognized%20the%20opportunity%20to%20scale%20the%20model%20fast%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20doing%20is%20somewhere%20between%20Netflix%20and%20TikTok%2C%26quot%3B%20Tepper%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20think%20there's%20some%20space%20in%20there%20for%20premium%20entertainment%2C%20but%20consumed%20in%20a%20different%20way%3A%20mobile%2C%20short%20form.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222217%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TrueShort%20screenshot%20of%20app%20showing%20it%20aims%20to%20make%20films%20in%20a%20full%20range%20of%20genres%20using%20AI.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0351be95396a3b6e41774f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222287%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrueShort%20started%20with%20true%20crime%20but%20aims%20to%20make%20AI%20films%20in%20a%20full%20range%20of%20genres%20over%20time.%3Cp%3ETrueShort%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Hollywood%20notables%20have%20been%20getting%20into%20verticals%20as%20traditional%20film%20and%20TV%20production%20has%20slowed.%20Film%20producer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fveyou-pitch-deck-hollywoods-tommy-harper-launches-micro-drama-app-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETommy%20Harper%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20launched%20a%20verticals%20app%20called%20VeYou%2C%20following%20similar%20moves%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhollywood-invests-micro-dramas-disney-fox-explore-the-format-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eex-Miramax%20CEO%20Bill%20Block%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Lloyd%20Braun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStreaming%20consulting%20firm%20Owl%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%20estimated%20vertical%20film%20apps%20generated%20%241.4%20billion%20in%20the%20US%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20micro-drama%20apps%20have%20also%20begun%20making%20films%20featuring%20AI%20characters%2C%20to%20mixed%20reviews%20from%20viewers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETepper%20started%20TrueShort%20with%20documentary-style%20true%20crime%20series.%20He%20said%20he%20thought%20these%20types%20of%20movies%20%E2%80%94%20with%20their%20mix%20of%20real%20archival%20footage%20and%20AI%20characters%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20more%20palatable%20for%20viewers.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20wants%20to%20branch%20out%20quickly%20to%20other%20genres%20as%20the%20quality%20improves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20plans%20to%20add%2060%20filmmakers%20and%20editors%20this%20year%2C%20on%20top%20of%20the%2020%20the%20company%20has%20now.%20High-quality%20animation%20can%20be%20made%20with%20AI%2C%20and%20live-action%20is%20getting%20there%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReducing%20cost-intensive%20film%20production%20is%20one%20of%20AI's%20big%20promises.%20TrueShort%20makes%20one%2020-%20to%2030-minute%20movie%20a%20week%2C%20using%20AI%20tools%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startups-netflix-marvel-lucasfilm-holllywood-deepfake-dubbing-vc-funding-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20like%20Eleven%20Labs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Midjourney.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20teams%20can%20produce%20a%20movie%20for%20%241%2C000%20to%20%243%2C000%20each%2C%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20typical%20%24100%2C000%20to%20%24300%2C000%20cost%20of%20a%20micro%20drama%20using%20human%20actors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20micro%20drama%20apps%20today%20are%20subscription-driven%20and%20rely%20heavily%20on%20paid%20marketing%20to%20get%20people%20to%20download%20their%20apps.%20Some%20industry%20insiders%20predict%20the%20model%20will%20shift%20toward%20ads%20as%20people%20get%20subscription%20fatigue%2C%20and%20that%20viewing%20will%20shift%20to%20apps%20like%20TikTok%20that%20already%20have%20large%20user%20bases.%20TikTok%20is%20casting%20actors%20to%20make%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-casting-actors-short-dramas-microdramas-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eown%20micro%20dramas%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20launching%20a%20micro%20drama%20feed%20in%20its%20app%20as%20well%20as%20a%20freestanding%20app%2C%20Pine%20Drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrueShort%20makes%20money%20through%20subscriptions%3A%20%2439.99%20a%20year%2C%20%2414.99%20a%20month%2C%20or%20%246.99%20a%20week.%20Tepper%20said%20he%20has%20no%20plans%20to%20sell%20ads%20and%20that%20the%20subscription%20model%20is%20working%20well%2C%20with%20the%20company%20on%20track%20to%20make%20money%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20%2410%20million%20a%20year%20by%20the%20end%20of%202026.%20The%20app%20relies%20on%20paid%20marketing%2C%20but%20Tepper%20said%20he's%20optimistic%20that%20as%20its%20quality%20improves%2C%20word%20of%20mouth%20will%20replace%20that%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20rely%20on%20paid%20ads%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20can%20sign%20up%20for%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Fcmo-insider%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20weekly%20marketing%20newsletter%20here%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkhosla-ventures-jeffrey-katzenberg-backing-trueshort-ai-vertical-film-app-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778669101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a037fdc58810e27922acdf8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkhosla-ventures-jeffrey-katzenberg-backing-trueshort-ai-vertical-film-app-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TrueShort%2C%20which%20makes%20AI%20vertical%20films%20for%20mobile%20phones%2C%20just%20raised%20%2412%20million%20from%20a%20who's%20who%20of%20Hollywood%20and%20tech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmoses%40insider.com%20(Lucia%20Moses)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22amp