0with%20Sequoia%20Capital%20on%20May%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20answers%20%E2%80%94%20including%20how%20he%20mostly%20runs%20the%20agents%20via%20his%20phone%20%E2%80%94%20highlighted%20how%20some%20Silicon%20Valley%20engineers%20are%20beginning%20to%20use%20AI%20systems%20less%20like%20chatbots%20and%20more%20like%20always-on%20autonomous%20assistants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20the%20Claude%20app%2C%20and%20if%20you%20open%20the%20Claude%20App%2C%20on%20the%20left-hand%20side%2C%20there's%20this%20little%20code%20tab%2C%20and%20I%20just%20have%20a%20bunch%20of%20sessions%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20while%20showing%20his%20phone%20to%20the%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20how%20many%20sessions%20he%20had%2C%20Cherny%20said%20he%20typically%20runs%20%26quot%3Bfive%20to%2010%20sessions%2C%26quot%3B%20each%20containing%20multiple%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUsually%2C%20every%20night%2C%20I%20have%20like%20a%20few%20thousand%20that%20are%20doing%20kind%20of%20deeper%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECherny%20said%20he%20relies%20heavily%20on%20two%20Claude%20Code%20features%20built%20for%20persistent%20automation%3A%20%2Floops%20and%20Routines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20users%20can%20schedule%20%2Floops%20locally%20via%20cron%2C%20while%20Routines%20run%20recurring%20tasks%20on%20a%20server%2C%20allowing%20engineers%20to%20keep%20agents%20working%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoders-keep-laptops-open-in-public-ai-agent-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etheir%20laptops%20are%20closed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20like%2C%20the%20coolest%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20haven't%20experimented%20with%20it%2C%20highly%20recommend%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20Cherny%20has%20shared%20how%20he%20uses%20his%20agents.%20In%20January%2C%20he%20shared%20his%20agentic%20setup%20on%20X%2C%20calling%20i