il%20trading%20activity%20has%20offered%20a%20cushion%20to%20the%20global%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rise%20in%20seaborne%20exports%20from%20the%20US%20and%20decline%20in%20imports%20into%20China%20has%20absorbed%209.3%20mb%2Fd%20of%20the%2012.3%20mb%2Fd%20YoY%20Middle%20East%20decline%2C%20shielding%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan%20Chase%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-avoid-big-decisions-when-tired-on-a-friday-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJamie%20Dimon%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20changes%20in%20US%20exports%20and%20China's%20imports%20may%20be%20way%20the%20Iran%20war%20%26quot%3Bhasn't%20been%20a%20severe%20thing%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20oil%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20noted%20that%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20conflict%20get%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20more%20serious%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20the%20day%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bbecomes%20a%20disaster%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20pushed%20further%20down%20the%20line.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20reported%20the%20oil%20market%20has%20lost%20nearly%20one%20billion%20barrels%20of%20supply%20due%20to%20the%20war%2C%20the%20firm%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20even%20if%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20reopened%20tomorrow%2C%20the%20market%20is%20set%20to%20lose%20another%20billion%20barrels%20in%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20normalize%20the%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20this%20is%20the%20largest%20oil%20supply%20disruption%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20oil%20market%20is%20neither%20an%20exaggeration%20nor%20controversial%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20firm%20underlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fcommodities%2Foil-price%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrent%20crude%3C%2Fa%3E%20traded%20around%20%24108%20per%20barrel%20on%20Tuesday%2C%2073%20days%20since%20the%20first%20US-Israel%20strikes%20on%20Iran%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fcommodities%2Foil-price%3Ftype%3Dwti%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWTI%20oil%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20settled%20near%20%24102.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20prices%20are%20well%20above%20prewar%20levels%2C%20but%20have%20pulled%20back%20from%20their%20recent%20peaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FePBRP%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22466%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPrices%20during%20the%20war%20have%20been%20relatively%20subdued%20compared%20to%20previous%20spikes%20driven%20by%20less%20significant%20disruptions%20to%20global%20oil%20flows.%20Morgan%20Stanley%20said%20prices%20aren't%20high%20when%20examined%20in%20historic%20terms.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBrent%20traded%20above%20%24100%2Fb%20throughout%20the%20four-year%20stretch%20from%202011%20to%202014%2C%20and%20reached%20%24130%2Fb%20in%20March%202022%20on%20a%20far%20smaller%20disruption%20than%20the%20one%20currently%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FLVnWL%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22464%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20called%20out%20the%20oil%20price%20moves%20in%202022%20when%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine.%20%26quot%3BOil%20prices%20have%20risen%2C%20but%20still%20failed%20to%20reach%20the%20levels%20of%202022%20-%20a%20much%20smaller%20disruption%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20obvious%20explanations%20for%20muted%20price%20increases%20in%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20view%20are%20the%20market's%20strong%20prewar%20oil%20surplus%20and%20investors%20pricing%20in%20a%20resolution%20coming%20shortly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategists%20say%20the%20the%20%26quot%3Bmore%20revealing%26quot%3B%20reasons%20behind%20the%20relatively%20muted%20high%20oil%20prices%20despite%20the%20historic%20market%20disruption%20of%20the%20ongoing%20Iran%20war%20are%20driven%20by%20trading%20activity%20from%20two%20global%20powers%3A%20the%20US%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rise%20in%20seaborne%20exports%20from%20the%20US%20and%20decline%20in%20imports%20into%20China%20has%20absorbed%209.3%20mb%2Fd%20of%20the%2012.3%20mb%2Fd%20YoY%20Middle%20East%20decline%2C%20shielding%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Crude%20oil%20seaborne%20net%20imports%2Fexports%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a03432858810e27922acb29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20lifted%20net%20exports%20while%20China%20cut%20net%20imports%2C%20offering%20a%20balance%20in%20the%20global%20oil%20trade.%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Stanley%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOil-on-water%20is%20rising%20again%2C%20not%20falling%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategist%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Stanley%20examined%20tanker%20tracking%20data%20and%20found%20that%20the%20global%20seaborne%20balance%20has%20actually%20loosened%20recently%20thanks%20to%20the%20import%20and%20export%20activity%20in%20the%20US%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2291dc2d5f-9e93-45a1-8490-718f01a41dbb%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20adds%20barrels%20to%20the%20market%2C%20boosting%20oil%20exports%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20oil%20producing%20countries%20led%20by%20the%20US%20have%20boosted%20seaborne%20exports%20more%20significantly%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategists%20examined%20exports%20from%20April%208%20to%20May%208%20in%202026%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20month%20period%20in%202025.%20They%20found%20that%20net%20exports%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20UAE%2C%20Kuwait%2C%20Iraq%2C%20Iran%2C%20Qatar%2C%20and%20Bahrain%20saw%20a%2012.3%20million%20barrel%20per%20day%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20this%20loss%20has%20been%20partially%20offset%20but%20increased%20exports%20from%20other%20producers%20exporting%20around%205.5%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20effort%20has%20been%20led%20by%20the%20US%2C%20which%20alone%20accounts%20for%203.8%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20offset%20on%20the%20export%20side%20is%20overwhelmingly%20a%20single-country%20story%3A%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20oil%20exporting%20countries%20have%20also%20lifted%20exports%2C%20but%20by%20smaller%20amounts.%20Canada%20was%20the%20second%20largest%20contributor%20with%200.4%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%2C%20followed%20by%20Argentina%20and%20Venezuela%20adding%200.2%20million%20barrels%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2efa374-ee1c-4f47-85ad-5719e4c9244a%5C%22%3EChina%20dampens%20demand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20demand%20side%2C%20some%20oil%20exporters%20have%20lowered%20net%20imports%2C%20China%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20month%20period%202026%20to%202025%20comparison%2C%20countries%20that%20typically%20import%20oil%20have%20cut%20their%20seaborne%20net%20imports%20by%2010.9%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%2C%20which%20exceeds%20the%20net%20contraction%20in%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20dynamic%20signals%20there%20there%20has%20been%20demand%20destruction%2C%20which%20could%20be%20driven%20by%20buyers%20holding%20off%20on%20purchases%20expecting%20the%20Strait%20to%20reopen%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20alone%20makes%20up%20half%20of%20the%20decrease%20in%20imports.%20The%20country%20imported%20around%2014%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20but%20today%20imports%20about%208.5%20million%20barrels%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20scale%20of%20the%20adjustment%20is%20remarkable%20and%2C%20in%20our%20view%2C%20this%20is%20the%20single%20most%20important%20component%20of%20the%20puzzle%2C%26quot%3B%20Morgan%20Stanley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESigns%20point%20to%20China%20having%20a%20hearty%20oil%20reserve%20that%20the%20country%20is%20drawing%20on%20as%20it%20dials%20back%20imports.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20isn't%20the%20only%20nation%20that's%20bringing%20in%20less%20oil.%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20India%20and%20Singapore%20have%20cut%20a%20collective%203.9%20million%20barrels%20per%20day.%20Europe%20and%20other%20refiners%20make%20up%20around%20the%201.5%20million%20barrel%20remaining%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-prices-us-exports-china-imports-trump-iran-war-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778663701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a03397dc9dd4cb81cda98ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-prices-us-exports-china-imports-trump-iran-war-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Morgan%20Stanley%20strategists%20say%20that%20oil%20prices%20are%20lower%20relative%20to%20other%20supply%20shocks%20thanks%20to%20two%20global%20forces%20working%20in%20tandem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nbuchanan%40insider.com%20(Naomi%20Buchanan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A98%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TVS%20Motor%20Q4%20result%3A%20Net%20profit%20jumps%2017.5%25%20to%20%E2%82%B9819.55%20cr%20on%20strong%20sales%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778663461000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.b